# Proposal B: Agentic Financial Compliance Agent

**HP + Morningstar AI Hackathon** | 4 Hours | HP ZGX Nano AI Station

---

## Overview

Build an AI agent that autonomously analyzes financial documents, checks compliance rules, and produces structured reports - running entirely on the ZGX Nano. Unlike a simple Q&A chatbot, your agent will reason, plan, select tools, and execute multi-step workflows on its own. Given a natural language compliance query, it will figure out what data to pull, what checks to run, and how to assemble the findings into a report.

---

## How This Differs from Proposal A

| Proposal A: RAG Research Assistant | Proposal B: Agentic Compliance Agent |
|------------------------------------|--------------------------------------|
| Single pipeline: retrieve context, generate answer | Multi-step: plan, call tools, observe results, refine |
| User asks a question, gets an answer | User states a goal, agent figures out the steps |
| Good starting point for teams newer to local AI | Better for teams already comfortable with RAG who want to push further |

Proposal B is more complex, but the payoff is bigger. Watching an agent autonomously reason through a compliance check - calling the right tools in the right order, logging every decision - is a different experience from a Q&A chatbot.

