## Choosing Between Proposal A and Proposal B

| Factor | Proposal A (RAG) | Proposal B (Agentic) |
|--------|-------------------|----------------------|
| Team experience | Good for teams newer to local AI / LLM development | Better for teams already comfortable with AI who want to push further |
| Complexity | Lower - single pipeline, predictable flow | Higher - multi-step reasoning, tool schema design, failure modes |
| Risk of not finishing | Low - most teams will complete the full pipeline | Medium - some teams may have 3-4 tools working vs. all 6, which is still a good demo |
| Relevance to Morningstar | High - research Q&A is a core workflow | Very high - compliance monitoring is a critical daily function |

Both work. If your team has built RAG systems before, Proposal B will be more engaging. If you're newer to local AI development, Proposal A gives a stronger foundation.
